ln Association over the past twenty-five years. And college and university introductory courses will find this book a valuable summary of, and introduction to, the major issues of the Civil War period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 7aHISTORY / United States / Civil War Period (1850-1877).2bisacsh1 aBerwanger, Eugene H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreiseth, Christopher N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFehrenbacher, Don E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerris, Norman B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGienapp, William E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHope Franklin, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHubbell, John T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyman, Harold M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcPherson, James M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiven, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaludan, Phillip S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVorenberg, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, T. Harry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZilversmit, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311074329640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329555540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823295555423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823295555/original  a978-3-11-074329-6  Ford